'''Defend Music''' is an independent [[music publisher (popular music)|music publishing]] company and music rights administrator based in [[Los Angeles]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.defendmusic.com/contact/|title=Defend Music - Contact|publisher=}}</ref> The firm is best known for publishing the songs of popular [[soul music]] group [[Sharon Jones & The Dap-Kings]] and other writers and artists on [[Daptone Records]], and publishes shares of hits by [[Jay-Z]], [[Black Eyed Peas]], [[Kaskade]] and others. [[Germans|German]] [[expatriate]] Michael Prommer started the company in 2004.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=ShAEAAAAMBAJ&lpg=PA43&ots=sLTzu6MbXs&dq=billboard%20michael%20prommer%20defend&pg=PA43#v=onepage&q=billboard%20michael%20prommer%20defend&f=false|title=Billboard|publisher=}}</ref>

In its early years, Defend also offered [[music distribution]] services had a [[record label]] that released music by [[Simian Mobile Disco]], [[9th Wonder]] and others.

Outside of North America, Defend's songs are sub-published by [[Kobalt Music Group|Kobalt]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.defendmusic.com/contact/|title=Defend Music - Contact|publisher=}}</ref>

