'''Iflix''', styled as '''iflix''', is a subscription [[video on demand]] (VOD) service focused on emerging markets. Its global headquarters are in [[Kuala Lumpur]], [[Malaysia]].<ref name="restored_0">{{Cite web|url = http://business.inquirer.net/201050/iflix-user-base-hits-300000-eyes-further-expansion|title = iflix user base hits 300,000, eyes further expansion|date = 21 October 2015|work = Philippine Daily Inquirer}}</ref> The site serves as a digital hosting and distribution platform for Western, Asian, and Middle Eastern TV shows and movies obtained through partnerships with over 150 studios and content distributors globally<ref name="restored_1">{{Cite web|url = http://www.mediabusinessasia.com/news_article.php?id=1707|title = iFLix Claims 1 Mil. Members|date = 11 December 2015|website = ''mediabusinessasia.com''|publisher = Media Business Asia}}</ref> including [[Metro-Goldwyn-Mayer]], [[The Walt Disney Company|Disney]], [[Warner Bros.|Warner Bros]], [[Paramount Pictures|Paramount]], [[NBCUniversal|NBC Universal]], [[Fox Broadcasting Company|Fox]], [[CBS]], [[BBC]], [[Sony Pictures]] and [[Discovery Communications|Discovery]].

iflix is currently available in 28 countries across Asia and Africa, including Malaysia, Indonesia, Philippines, Brunei, Thailand, Vietnam, Cambodia, Myanmar, Pakistan, Nepal, Bangladesh, Sri Lanka, Maldives, Saudi Arabia, Kuwait, Bahrain, Jordan, Iraq, Lebanon, Egypt, Sudan, Nigeria, Kenya, Ghana, Zimbabwe, Tanzania, Morocco and Uganda.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.digitaltveurope.net/689232/iflix-expands-into-mena/|title=Iflix expands into MENA " Digital TV Europe|website=''digitaltveurope.net''|access-date=29 May 2017}}</ref> As of December 2017, iflix has more than 6.5&nbsp;million subscribers on its service.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2017/digital/asia/wrong-assumptions-about-asian-streaming-video-iflix-mark-britt-1202622591/|title='Lose All Your Assumptions About Asian Streaming,' Says Iflix CEO Mark Britt}}</ref>

==History==

=== Founding and Establishment ===
iflix was founded by [[Patrick Grove]], CEO of [[Catcha Group]], Mark Britt and Evolution Media, a merchant bank focused on the media, sports, and entertainment industries.<ref name=":2">{{Cite web|url=https://www.techinasia.com/iflix-brings-hollywood-to-southeast-asia|title=With iFlix, Patrick Grove wants to bring the best of Hollywood to Southeast Asia|date=10 March 2015|website=Tech in Asia|publisher=techinasia.com}}</ref> iflix was created for the rapidly growing, emerging middle-class population and their increasing demand for entertainment content. The company set out to address a certain set of conditions, which tend to exist universally across emerging markets – prevalence of [[piracy]], inconsistent infrastructure, inconsistent quality and distribution of internet connectivity, expensive and limited mobile data, low paid television penetration, low credit-card penetration and a lack of familiarity with online payment options – through technology and commercial partnerships.

In April 2015, iflix announced the completion of a $30&nbsp;million round of funding, led by leading international investment firm, Catcha Group and [[Philippine Long Distance Telephone Company]] (PLDT), the largest integrated telecommunications company in the Philippines.<ref>{{Cite web|url = https://www.iflix.com/images/media/press/iflix%20_raises_30_million.pdf|title = IFLIX RAISES $30M, PRIMED FOR GROWTH|date = 23 April 2015|website = Media Room|publisher = iflix}}</ref> The company launched its service in Malaysia and the Philippines one month later,<ref>{{Cite web|url = https://www.iflix.com/images/media/press/iflix_now_available.pdf|title = iFLIX NOW AVAILABLE|date = 27 May 2015|website = Media Room|publisher = iflix}}</ref> where they additionally announced the formation of its Advisory Board, composed of Hollywood business and creative leaders.<ref>{{Cite web|url = https://www.iflix.com/images/media/press/iflix_Announces_Advisory_Board.pdf|title = iFLIX ANNOUNCES ADVISORY BOARD|date = 22 May 2015|website = Media Room|publisher = iflix}}</ref> By July, iflix recorded over 100,000 subscribers, becoming Southeast Asia's fastest growing Internet TV service.<ref name="restored_4">{{Cite web|url = https://www.iflix.com/images/media/press/23_07_2015_iflix_SEAs_Fastest_Growing.pdf|title = iFLIX RECORDS OVER 100,000 SUBSCRIBERS AS SOUTHEAST ASIA'S FASTEST GROWING INTERNET TV SERVICE|date = 23 July 2015|website = Media Room|publisher = iflix}}</ref> Within the 12-week trial phase of its official launch in Thailand in November, iflix drew close to 200,000 subscribers.<ref name="restored_5">{{Cite web|url = https://www.iflix.com/images/media/press/iflix-Launches-in-Thailand-and-Welcomes-Top-Celebs-to-the-iflix-Family.pdf|title = iFLIX OFFICIALLY LAUNCHES IN THAILAND & WELCOMES TOP CELEBS TO THE iFLIX FAMILY|date = 30 November 2015|website = Media Room|publisher = iflix}}</ref>

In March 2016, iflix attracted a $45-million investment from European [[pay-TV]] giant [[Sky plc]].<ref>'Sky Invests $45 Million in Southeast Asian Streaming Service Iflix', Wall Street Journal 9 March 2016 https://www.wsj.com/articles/sky-invests-45-million-in-southeast-asian-streaming-service-iflix-1457541253</ref> In June, iflix announced its official launch in Indonesia and in August 2016, iflix announced its official launch in Sri Lanka.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.businessinsider.co.id/sri-lanka-gets-iflix-thousands-worlds-best-tv-shows-movies/#bT6EkRpQWXhZFiEd.97|title=Sri Lanka gets iflix and thousands of the world's best TV shows and movies – Business Insider|date=2 August 2016|access-date=2 August 2016}}</ref> It announced its official launch in Brunei on September,<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.thehive.asia/2016/09/iflix-is-now-available-in-brunei.html|title=iflix is now available in Brunei!|last=TheHive|newspaper=TheHive.Asia|access-date=15 February 2017}}</ref> and the Maldives in November.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.mumbrella.asia/2016/11/iflix-launches-maldives/|title=Iflix launches in the Maldives – Mumbrella Asia|date=21 November 2016|newspaper=Mumbrella Asia|access-date=15 February 2017}}</ref>

In January 2017, iflix announced its official launch in Pakistan.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://variety.com/2017/tv/asia/iflix-launches-in-pakistan-1201963285/amp/|title=Streaming Service Iflix Launches in Pakistan|date=19 January 2017|newspaper=Variety|access-date=15 February 2017}}</ref>

In February 2017, iflix announced its official launch in Vietnam.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.thesaigontimes.vn/156436/Dich-vu-truyen-hinh-iFlix-vao-thi-truong-Viet-Nam.html|title=Dịch vụ truyền hình iFlix vào thị trường Việt Nam|date=24 January 2017|newspaper=The Saigon Times|access-date=24 January 2017|language=Vietnamese}}</ref> That same month the company announced a joint venture with [[Zain Group|Zain]], leading telecommunications group in the Middle East and Africa, establishing iflix Arabia.<ref name="iflix.com">https://www.iflix.com/images/media/press/15Feb17_iflix_and_Zain_establish_iflix_Arabia.pdf</ref>

In March 2017, iflix announced its official launch in Myanmar.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.nationmultimedia.com/news/business/aec/30308970|title=Iflix launches video on demand in Myanmar, VN  |work=The Nation|access-date=15 April 2017}}</ref>

In April 2017, iflix went live in 8 countries in MENA.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/asian-streaming-service-iflix-expands-middle-east-north-africa-997546|title=Asian Streaming Service Iflix Expands into Middle East, North Africa (Exclusive)}}</ref> and in October 2017, iflix launched in Nepal.<ref>https://www.iflix.com/images/media/press/12Oct2017_iflix_is_Now_Available_in_Nepal_Final.pdf</ref>

In June 2017, iflix announced the establishment of iflix Africa. iflix Africa is headquartered in [[Cape Town]], South Africa and trades commercially as 'iflix', with launches in Nigeria, Kenya and Ghana, Sudan and Zimbabwe.<ref>https://www.iflix.com/images/media/press/1Jun17_iflix_Africa.pdf</ref>

iflix launched in Bangladesh in November 2017. [[Robi]] and [[Airtel Bangladesh|Airtel]] customers get 3 months free access when signing up.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.thedailystar.net/arts-entertainment/event/iflix-launches-bangladesh-1486753|title=iflix launches in Bangladesh|date=6 November 2017|work=The Daily Star|access-date=13 November 2017}}</ref>

iflix launched its own creative production business for short-form video content Studio2:15 in March 2018, its first production was ''Cupid Co.'' in April 2018. <ref name="Studio2:15">{{Cite news|url=https://blog.iflix.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/2018.03.29-iflix-Launches-Studio215-Led-by-Digital-Media-Trailblazer-Craig-Galvin.pdf|title=IFLIX LAUNCHES STUDIO 2:15 LED BY DIGITAL MEDIA TRAILBLAZER, CRAIG GALVIN|work=iflix|date=March 29, 2018|accessdate=October 7, 2018}}</ref>


=== Management ===
In July 2016, former CEO of StockUnlimited Christian Toksvig joined as Head of International Business Development. Founder of Iktomi Nader Sobhan joined as Head of Middle East and North Africa and in November 2017, he transitioned into the role of Strategic Advisor, working closely with Group CEO Mark Britt.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://worldscreen.com/tvmiddleeastafrica/iflix-names-telecom-exec-john-saad-as-ceo-of-mena/|title=Iflix Names Telecom Exec John Saad as CEO of MENA}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.iflix.com/images/media/press/iflix_adds_exec_July7.pdf|title=iflix Adds to Executive Team, Primed for International Expansion|website=}}</ref>

In October 2016, Marc Barnett joined iflix Group as Chief Operating Officer.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://mumbrella.com.au/marc-barnett-leaves-bohemia-role-asian-streaming-firm-iflix-404478|title=Marc Barnett leaves Bohemia for role at Asian streaming firm iFlix – Mumbrella|date=27 October 2016}}</ref>

In January 2017, former head of technology for all of Walt Disney's businesses outside of the United States, Emmanuel Frenehard, joined iflix as Chief Technology Officer of iflix Group.<ref>https://www.iflix.com/images/media/press/7Nov16_CTO_OF_DISNEY_INTERNATIONAL_EMMANUEL_FRENEHARD_JOINS_IFLIX.pdf</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.digitalnewsasia.com/business/cto-disney-international-emmanuel-frenehard-joins-iflix|title=CTO of Disney International, Emmanuel Frenehard joins iflix|date=7 November 2016}}</ref>

In March 2017, former VP, Global Television at Netflix Sean Carey was appointed the new Chief Content Officer, in place of James Bridges.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://variety.com/2017/digital/asia/iflix-appoints-netflix-sean-carey-1202007495/|title=Asian Video Platform Iflix Hires Netflix's Sean Carey as Content Head|last=Frater|first=Patrick|date=13 March 2017|work=Variety|access-date=15 April 2017}}</ref>

In September 2017, the company appointed Sky PLC executive, Anil Jhingan as Chief Financial and Commercial Officer.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dailymirror.lk/article/iflix-appoints-Anil-Jhingan-as-new-Chief-Commercial-and-Financial-Officer-136655.html/|title=iflix appoints Anil Jhingan as new Chief Commercial and Financial Officer}}</ref>

In November 2017, iflix appointed telecommunications executive John Saad as CEO of iflix MENA.<ref>https://www.iflix.com/images/media/press/iflixAppoints_John_Saad_as_CEO_of_iflix_MENA_Final.pdf</ref>

In March 2018, iflix appointed digital media trailblazer Craig Galvin to become the head of the company's creative production business for short-form video content, Studio2:15. <ref name="Studio2:15" />

==Strategies==

===Localisation===
iflix's local content strategy focuses on first-run local movies and original programming. iflix has greenlit a number of projects which underpin this  strategy and support home-grown talent.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://adobomagazine.com/digital-news/iflix-continues-expand-ph-and-asia-localized-content|title=iflix continues to expand in PH and Asia with localized content}}</ref> The emphasis on localisation includes dubbing and sub-titling content, as well as engaging local content creators to produce compelling local stories through their work.<ref>{{cite web|last=Lee|first=Liz|url=https://www.dealstreetasia.com/stories/iflix-44962/|title=Malaysia: iflix aims for Africa, Middle East markets, after taking on Indonesia|work=Deal Street Asia|date=21 June 2016|access-date=1 February 2018}}</ref>

===Tackling Piracy===
The company says it is an alternative that is better, safer and more convenient than piracy, and that it further respects local cultural and religious standards and preferences in each market with a strategy to build and support the industry ecosystem, to generate jobs in the creative field.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/susancunningham/2017/03/01/malaysia-patrick-grove-plans-to-go-global-with-iflix-video-on-demand/|title= Malaysia's Patrick Grove Aims To Go Global With Iflix Video-On-Demand}}</ref>

==Partnerships==
iflix works with selected studios and telecommunications companies both regionally and worldwide, having partnerships with PLDT Group for commercial distribution<ref>{{Cite web|url = https://www.iflix.com/images/media/press/po.st_iflixPLDTJune19.pdf|title = iFLIX FORMS EXCLUSIVE STRATEGIC PARTNERSHIP WITH PLDT GROUP|date = 19 June 2015|website = Media Room|publisher = iflix}}</ref> and the landmark content partnerships with a number of Hollywood's studios; including [[The Walt Disney Company]],<ref>{{Cite web|url = https://www.iflix.com/images/media/press/iflix_Signs_Landmark_Content_Agreement_with_Disney.pdf|title = iFLIX SIGNS LANDMARK CONTENT AGREEMENT WITH DISNEY|date = 23 June 2015|website = Media Room|publisher = iflix}}</ref> [[Metro-Goldwyn-Mayer]] (MGM),<ref>{{Cite web|url = https://www.iflix.com/images/media/press/30062015_iflix_Announces_Multi_Year_Content_Agreement_with_MGM.pdf|title = iFLIX ANNOUNCES MULTI-YEAR CONTENT AGREEMENT WITH METRO-GOLDWYN-MAYER|date = 30 June 2015|website = Media Room|publisher = iflix}}</ref> [[Paramount Pictures]],<ref>{{Cite web|url = https://www.iflix.com/images/media/press/30062015_iflix_Secures_Topline_licensing_deal_with_Paramount.pdf|title = iFLIX SECURES TOPLINE LICENSING DEAL WITH PARAMOUNT PICTURES|date = 30 June 2015|website = Media Room|publisher = iflix}}</ref> [[Warner Bros.|Warner Bros]],<ref name="restored_3">{{Cite web|url = https://www.iflix.com/images/media/press/12.5.2015_iflix%20secures%20topline%20content%20deals_FINAL.pdf|title = IFLIX SECURES TOPLINE CONTENT DEALS WITH FOX, BBC AND WARNER BROS.|date = 12 May 2015|website = Media Room|publisher = iflix}}</ref> [[Fox Broadcasting Company|Fox]],<ref name="restored_3"/> and [[Starz]].<ref>{{Cite web|url = https://www.iflix.com/images/media/press/30062015_iflix_Premiere_Home_to_Black_Sails.pdf|title = iFLIX PREMIERE HOME TO TELEVISION PHENOMENON FROM STARZ, BLACK SAILS|date = 30 June 2015|website = Media Room|publisher = iflix}}</ref> It also announced together with Vimond Media Solutions, which plans to establish a jointly operated development centre in Kuala Lumpur.<ref>{{Cite web|url = https://www.iflix.com/images/media/press/po.st_iflixVimondJune2.pdf|title = iFLIX AND VIMOND ESTABLISH JOINT DEVELOPMENT CENTRE IN KUALA LUMPUR|date = 2 June 2015|website = Media Room|publisher = iflix}}</ref>

In August 2015, iflix announced that MGM, had become an investor in the business. MGM's Chairman and Chief Executive Officer Gary Barber sits on iflix's Advisory Board and the companies' extensive multi-year content licensing partnership.<ref>{{Cite web|url = https://www.iflix.com/images/media/press/MGM_Joins_iflix_as_Strategic_Investor_Aug20.pdf|title = MGM JOINS iFLIX FAMILY AS STRATEGIC INVESTOR|date = 20 August 2015|website = Media Room|publisher = iflix}}</ref>

In September 2015, iflix entered into an agreement with Malaysian telecommunications giant, [[Digi Telecommunications|Digi Telecommunication Sdn Bhd (Digi)]] to provide iflix's service to Digi customers in Malaysia.<ref>{{Cite web|url = https://www.iflix.com/images/media/press/02092015_iflix_and_Digi_Partnership.pdf|title = iFLIX LAUNCHES STRATEGIC PARTNERSHIP WITH DIGI|date = 2 September 2015|website = Media Room|publisher = iflix}}</ref>

In December 2015, iflix announced partnerships in Malaysia and the Philippines with leading telecommunications providers, [[Smart Communications]] (Smart) and [[Philippine Long Distance Telephone Company]] (PLDT) in the Philippines and [[Telekom Malaysia]] (TM) in Malaysia. iflix will provide its service to over 70 million Smart and PLDT HOME customers in the Philippines for free.<ref name="restored_6">{{Cite web|url = https://www.iflix.com/images/media/press/Dec14_iflix_Partners_with_Smart-PLDT.pdf|title = iflix, PLDT and SMART Share the Gift of Entertainment|date = 14 December 2015|website = Media Room|publisher = iflix}}</ref> In conjunction with Telekom Malaysia (TM), all TM Unifi and select Streamyx customers are offered a free 12-month iflix subscriptions.<ref name="restored_7">{{Cite web|url = https://www.iflix.com/images/media/press/iflix_Partners_with_TM.pdf|title = iflix Launches Landmark Partnership with Telekom Malaysia|date = 4 December 2015|website = Media Room|publisher = iflix}}</ref>

In April 2016, iflix announced partnership with leading telecommunications services company in Indonesia, [[Telkom Indonesia]], and Indonesian network provider [[Indosat Ooredoo]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.telkom.co.id/indihome-hadirkan-tv-streaming-iflix.html|title=TELKOM – PT. Telekomunikasi Indonesia Tbk|website=''telkom.co.id''|access-date=3 August 2016}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://inet.detik.com/read/2016/04/28/085058/3198529/317/setelah-telkom-iflix-hadir-di-indosat-ooredoo|title=Setelah Telkom, Iflix Hadir di Indosat Ooredoo|access-date=3 August 2016}}</ref> On 18 November, iflix launched its services in the Maldives in collaboration with the flagship telecommunication services provider in the country, [[Dhiraagu]],. In September 2017, iflix entered Bangladeshi market through the partnership with the third leading telecommunication service provider of the country, [[Robi]].

In February 2017, iflix announced a joint venture with [[Zain Group|Zain]], leading telecommunications group in the Middle East and Africa, establishing iflix Arabia.<ref name="iflix.com"/>

In January 2018, iflix announced a joint venture with [[Football Malaysia LLP]] to develop and produce new content formats, competitions and live stream matches, including Liga Super, Piala Malaysia, marquee Piala FA and selected Liga Premier matches on a dedicated "Football Malaysia on iflix" channel.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.goal.com/en-my/news/malaysian-football-be-available-iflix/1dfo8b2sky5yv16dp7jy4ih45s|title=Malaysian Football to be Available on iflix}}</ref>

== Celebrity Partners ==

Several notable celebrities have invested in iflix. In July 2015, Malaysian actress [[Maya Karin]] and TV host [[Sazzy Falak]] joined iflix as ambassadors and shareholders.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ohsem.me/2016/05/iflix-1-year-birthday-bash-maya-karin-brand-ambassador/|title=iFlix 1 Year Birthday Bash With Maya Karin As Brand Ambassador|date=25 May 2016|access-date=21 July 2016}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.iflix.com/images/media/press/Layan_Raya_iflix_Style_with_Maya_Karin_final.pdf|title=Layan Raya iflix Style with Maya Karin|website=}}</ref> In November of the same year, iflix welcomed Philippine celebrities [[Iza Calzado]], [[Jasmine Curtis-Smith]], [[Ruffa Gutierrez]], [[Raymond Gutierrez]], Richard Gutierrez, JM Rodriguez and [[Karylle]] Tatlonghari-Yuzon as partners in the business.<ref>{{Cite web|url = https://www.iflix.com/images/media/press/TOP_PHILIPPINES_CELEBS_JOIN_TEAM_IFLIX.pdf|title = Top Philippine Celebrities Join Team iflix|date = 16 November 2015|website = Media Room|publisher = iflix}}</ref> Thai celebrities; including actresses 'Jieb' Sopidnapa Chumpanee and [[Phiyada Akkraseranee|'Aom' Phiyada Akkraseranee]], 'Jeab' Lalana Kongtoranin, Note Panayanggool and 'Paule' Ponphan Sittinawawit also joined the company as both investors and advisors in the curation of new content for online viewers.<ref name="restored_5" /> In September 2017, Pakistan's biggest rockstar, [[Ali Zafar]], joined iflix as a celebrity parther.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://tribune.com.pk/story/1511351/pakistans-biggest-rock-star-ali-zafar-joins-team-iflix/|title=Pakistan's biggest rock star, Ali Zafar, joins team iflix}}</ref> In January 2018, Myanmar Academy Award-winning actress, [[Phway Phway]], joined iflix as a celebrity partner.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=La4DzWtH8EE|title=ေဖြးေဖြး ႏွင့္ iflix တို႔အတူ လက္တြဲမယ့္ Partner Launch|last=Myanmar Celebrity|date=29 January 2018|via=YouTube}}</ref>

