===Live Sports===
In May 2017, iflix streams Indonesia's [[Liga 1 (Indonesia)|Liga 1]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.iflix.com/images/media/press/31May17_Live_Streaming.pdf|title=IFLIX LAUNCHES LIVE FOOTBALL STREAMING IN INDONESIA WITH TVONE}}</ref> and the [[Floyd Mayweather Jr. vs. Conor McGregor]] fight in Indonesia,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://coconuts.co/jakarta/lifestyle/watch-mayweather-vs-mcgregor-jakarta-stream-free-anywhere-indonesia/|title=Where to watch Mayweather vs McGregor in Jakarta (or stream it for free anywhere in Indonesia!)}}</ref> and the [[2017 T10 Cricket League]] in Bangladesh.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.robi.com.bd/media-room/press-release/t10-cricket-league--live-on-iflix?lang=eng|title=T10 Cricket League – LIVE on IFLIX}}</ref>

A year later, iflix launched the “Football Malaysia on iflix” channel to live stream [[Malaysia Super League]], [[Malaysia Cup]] and marquee [[Malaysia FA Cup]] matches in Malaysia.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.foxsportsasia.com/football/asian-football/788671/malaysian-football-may-have-just-made-the-best-signing-ever/|title=Malaysian Football May Have Just Made the Best Signing Ever}}</ref> 

Later in September 2018, iflix streams [[University Athletic Association of the Philippines|UAAP]] men's basketball games in the Philippines.

In November 2018, iflix shows all [[Indonesian Basketball League]] games live in Indonesia, via both iflix LIVE channels : [[TvOne (Indonesia)|tvOne]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.topskor.id/detail/87053/Yes-tvONE-Siarkan-Pertandingan-IBL-Pertamax-201819|title=Yes! tvONE Siarkan Pertandingan IBL Pertamax 2018/19|last=topskor.id|website=TOPSKOR|language=en-US|access-date=2018-12-01}}</ref> (one game per series only, on Saturday night) and [[Indonesia Digital HOME|Usee Prime]]<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://twitter.com/UseeTVcom/status/1066693197118824448|title=UseeTV on Twitter|work=Twitter|access-date=2018-12-01|language=en}}</ref>.

==Features==

=== Channels ===
In August 2017, iflix launched Channels to showcase entertainment studios and brands, along with user'sʼ favourite content genres.
The feature includes personalised onboarding, and recommendations based on user's preferences and viewing history.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.interaksyon.com/iflix-launches-new-channels-feature/|title=iFlix launches new Channels feature|date=27 September 2017}}</ref>

=== Playlists ===
In August 2016, iflix launched its 'Playlists' feature, consisting of curated playlists of film productions from over 150 celebrities in the Southeast Asia, as well as 'Collections' based on moods and popular themes. Notable celebrities on 'Playlists' include [[Afdlin Shauki]], [[Amber Chia]], [[Ashraf Sinclair]], Michelle Ziudith and 'Ploy' Ployphan Taveerat.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.nst.com.my/news/2016/09/170043/iflix-launches-playlists-feature|title=Iflix launches playlists feature|access-date=5 September 2016}}</ref>

=== Download and Watch Offline ===
The service also offers the option of offline viewing to its members through its 'Download and Watch Offline' feature, where subscribers can download content without a Wi-Fi connection and without mobile data to their [[Android (operating system)|Android]] and [[IOS]] devices. Content can be downloaded in either "low", "medium" or "high" quality formats.<ref>{{Cite web|url = https://www.iflix.com/images/media/press/Nov24_iflix_launches_DWO.pdf|title = iFLIX LAUNCHES DOWNLOAD AND WATCH OFFLINE FEATURE|date = 24 November 2015|website = Media Room|publisher = iflix}}</ref>

=== High Definition ===
In March 2017, iflix rolled out its service in HD, with all new shows published on the platform available in HD.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.thestar.com.my/tech/tech-news/2017/03/02/iflix-goes-hd/|title=iflix goes HD – Tech News {{!}} The Star Online|website=The Star|location=Malaysia|access-date=29 May 2017}}</ref>

=== iflixFREE, iflixVIP and iflix LIVE ===
In April 2018, iflix CEO Mark Britt announced that they shift from its traditional subscription-only model into two tiers as part of its revamp, they named iflixFREE, iflixVIP and iflix LIVE. The free tier is an [[Advertising|ad-supported]] free service which features a curated Movie of the Day, premium short-form content, promotional episodes and pilots from premium TV series and movies, premium international and local TV series for free viewing and original programming. The VIP tier is an ad-free, subscription-only service which includes premium access to hundreds of movies and TV shows from local and international countries. The company also announced that they will launching iflix LIVE, a live hub which features live streaming of linear local over-the-air and Pay TV channels across both tiers. <ref>{{Cite web|url = https://blog.iflix.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/iflix-3.0_APOS_final.pdf|title = IFLIX 3.0|date = 26 April 2018|website = Media Room|publisher = iflix}}</ref>

